**Describe your issue**

![image](https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/assets/184182/1a080420-1715-47cd-a9c7-b93d6cc04219)

The issue is that the default variables get set globally and do not respect the `important` config var.

In particular, currently with `optimizeUniversalDefaults: true` and `important: ".scoped-down",`, we get:
```css
:is(.ring) {
  --tw-ring-inset:  ;
  --tw-ring-offset-width: 0px;
  --tw-ring-offset-color: #fff;
  --tw-ring-color: rgb(59 130 246 / 0.5);
  --tw-ring-offset-shadow: 0 0 #0000;
  --tw-ring-shadow: 0 0 #0000;
  --tw-shadow: 0 0 #0000;
  --tw-shadow-colored: 0 0 #0000;
}
```
But I would like to see:
```css
.scoped-down :is(.ring) {
  --tw-ring-inset:  ;
  --tw-ring-offset-width: 0px;
  --tw-ring-offset-color: #fff;
  --tw-ring-color: rgb(59 130 246 / 0.5);
  --tw-ring-offset-shadow: 0 0 #0000;
  --tw-ring-shadow: 0 0 #0000;
  --tw-shadow: 0 0 #0000;
  --tw-shadow-colored: 0 0 #0000;
}
```


Note, that without the experimental `optimizeUniversalDefaults`, the variables would be set on every element.

